d 'MMQRTEST': module to provide  specification and diagnostic tests for MM-QR location-scale panel quantile models (Machado and Santos Silva 2019; Canay 2011)
d
d     mmqrtest provides the testing toolbox that Machado and Santos
d Silva (2019) call for but do not develop.    Their
d method-of-moments quantile regression (MM-QR) is built on a
d conditional location-scale model, and the    authors note that
d "although we do not develop such tests here, it is possible to
d test the assumption that    the covariates only affect the
d location and scale functions" (sec. 1) and that such tests "can
d be	constructed as tests for overidentifying restrictions, but
d it may be possible to develop simpler    regression-based
d procedures" (sec. 7).  mmqrtest implements that program: every
d maintained assumption of the	  MM-QR panel model is mapped to a
d computable diagnostic with a clear verdict, publication-style
d tables, and	 optional graphs. 
d
d KW: method of moments
d KW: quantile regression
d KW: tests
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260612
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f mmqrtest.ado
f mmqrtest_canay.sthp
f mmqrtest_distfe.sthlp
f mmqrtest_guide.sthlp
f mmqrtest_postestimation.sthlp
f mmqrtest_scalepos.sthlp
f mmqrtest_scalerel.sthlp
f mmqrtest_spec.sthlp
f mmqrtest.sthlp
f mmqrtest_example.do
